# Important Definitions

## Type Casting

The process of converting one data type into another.

---

## Widening

Automatic conversion from a smaller data type to a larger data type.

---

## Narrowing

Manual conversion from a larger data type to a smaller data type.

---

## Data Loss

Loss of information during type conversion.

---

## Type Promotion

Automatic conversion of smaller data types (such as `byte` and `short`) to `int` during arithmetic operations.

