# Common Interview Mistakes

❌

```java
double d = 10.5;

int x = d;
```

Wrong.

---

✅

```java
int x = (int)d;
```

Correct.

---

❌ Thinking Java rounds values during narrowing.

Example

```java
(int)99.99
```

Output

```
99
```

Not

```
100
```

Java truncates the decimal part.

---

❌ Assuming widening always changes the value.

Example

```java
int x = 20;

double y = x;
```

The numeric value remains the same; only its representation changes.

